                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14189522" author="tveronezi" created="Thu, 30 Oct 2014 02:37:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch reads byte by byte until we read all our 4 important ones.&lt;br/&gt;
According to the &lt;a href=&quot;http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/io/InputStream.html#read(byte[],%20int,%20int)&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Java API&lt;/a&gt;, &quot;read&quot; might not read all the bytes in one single shot. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14189989" author="tveronezi" created="Thu, 30 Oct 2014 12:20:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12678165/12678165_make_sure_we_read_all_bytes_2.patch&quot; title=&quot;make_sure_we_read_all_bytes_2.patch attached to JOHNZON-17&quot;&gt;make_sure_we_read_all_bytes_2.patch&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; uses &quot;read()&quot; instead of &quot;read(...)&quot;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14190117" author="salyh" created="Thu, 30 Oct 2014 14:26:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the second patch looks good (first had a problem with \0 byte sequences), thanks a lot&lt;br/&gt;
will apply soon in addition with a testcase&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14190127" author="tveronezi" created="Thu, 30 Oct 2014 14:32:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Hendrik, thanks!&lt;br/&gt;
Please note the line..&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;-                inputStream.unread(utfBytes,0,read);
+                inputStream.unread(utfBytes);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I guess we should replace &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;inputStream.unread(utfBytes);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;by &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;inputStream.unread(utfBytes, 0, utfBytes.length);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can you check that out for me? I won&apos;t be able to do it before 20:00 EST today.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14191776" author="salyh" created="Fri, 31 Oct 2014 13:06:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;applied, thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14209730" author="salyh" created="Thu, 13 Nov 2014 13:16:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Preparing release 0.2-incubating&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
